<title>JAPAN: Dai-Ichi Kangyo reveals problem loans.</title>
<headline>Dai-Ichi Kangyo reveals problem loans.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dai-Ichi Kangyo Bank Ltd has disclosed its restructured loans (in billions of yen unless specified):</p>
<p>					end-Mar 97     end-Mar 96</p>
<p>  Restructured loans	    181.7	    233.5</p>
<p>  Bad loans			 328.1	    295.4</p>
<p>  Non-performing loans	  823.6	    849.7</p>
<p>  Loans to troubled clients   101.1	    455.7</p>
<p>  Total problem loans	    1.43 trln	1.83 trln</p>
<p>Restructured loans are those on which interest rates have been cut to help corporate restructuring. Bad loans are to bankrupt firms and non-performing are those with interest payments in arrears by six months or more. Loans to troubled clients are mainly to the bank's non-bank affiliates.</p>
</text>
